<p>Under tort law each member of a <strong>JOINT ENTERPRISE</strong> is <strong>vicariously liable</strong> for all torts committed by other members <strong>within the scope</strong> of the enterprise relationship.    </p>
<p>A joint enterprise is one in which two or more parties <strong>agree to work together</strong> for <strong>mutual benefit </strong>and each shares equal rights of control over assets and activities. </p>
